# Development Workflow

- **Spec-driven.** Every feature follows: Specify → Clarify → Plan → Tasks → Implement.
- **One feature at a time.** No parallel feature development.
- **Scope is additive.** Don't rewrite earlier features when adding new ones.
- **Constitution wins.** If a request conflicts with `.specify/memory/constitution.md`, the constitution wins unless formally amended.

# Project Constraints

- **Multi-user, invite-only.** Friend Release (in progress) adds NextAuth.js v5 auth + per-user data isolation. Constitution amended 2026-03-21. See `.specify/specs/friend-release/spec.md`.
- **Desktop only.** No mobile app. No public registration — admin creates all accounts manually.
- **SQLite + Docker.** Data persisted via volume mount. No external cloud services.
- **Stay in your lane.** Do not touch ports 8000 or 5173, or modify anything outside the `Life App/` folder.

# Key Documentation

Before starting work on a new feature, read these docs:

- `ROADMAP.md` — feature status and what's built
- `.specify/memory/constitution.md` — governing principles
- `specs/master/data-model.md` — database schema
- `specs/master/contracts/api-routes.md` — API surface
- `specs/master/tasks.md` — completed work log
- `.specify/specs/friend-release/spec.md` + `tasks.md` — active feature (multi-user auth)
